  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Config Hadoop for Pseudo Distributed Mode]]></title>
    <link href="http://andylinid45.github.io/blog/2015/08/21/config-hadoop-for-pseudo-distributed-mode/"/>
    <updated>2015-08-21T17:17:03+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://andylinid45.github.io/blog/2015/08/21/config-hadoop-for-pseudo-distributed-mode</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>install ssh</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>sudo apt-get install openssh-client=1:6.6p1-2ubuntu1
</span><span class='line'>sudo apt-get install openssh-server
</span><span class='line'>ssh-keygen
</span><span class='line'>cp .ssh/id_rsa.pub .ssh/authorized_keys
</span><span class='line'>ssh localhost</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo nano /opt/hadoop/conf/core-site.xml</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;property&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;name&gt;fs.default.name&lt;/name&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;value&gt;hdfs://localhost:9000&lt;/value&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;/property&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;property&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;name&gt;hadoop.tmp.dir&lt;/name&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;value&gt;/var/lib/hadoop&lt;/value&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;/property&gt;</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo nano /opt/hadoop/conf/hdfs-site.xml</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;property&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;name&gt;dfs.replication&lt;/name&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;value&gt;1&lt;/value&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;/property&gt;</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>sudo nano /opt/hadoop/conf/mapred-site.xml</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>&lt;property&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;name&gt;mapred.job.tracker&lt;/name&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;value&gt;localhost:9001&lt;/value&gt;
</span><span class='line'>&lt;/property&gt;</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>make temp dir for hadoop</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>sudo mkdir /var/lib/hadoop
</span><span class='line'>sudo chmod 777 /var/lib/hadoop</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>make log dir for hadoop</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>sudo mkdir /opt/hadoop/logs 
</span><span class='line'>sudo chmod 777 /opt/hadoop/logs/</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>run just for the first time to format file system</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>hadoop namenode -format</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>start it</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>start-dfs.sh
</span><span class='line'>start-mapred.sh
</span><span class='line'>hadoop fs -ls /  # have a test</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>web UI for it</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>http://localhost:50030/
</span><span class='line'>http://localhost:50070/</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>



]]></content>
  </entry>
  
